{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2016}} '''Karine Charlebois''' (born August 18, 1974 in [[Sainte-Thérèse, Quebec]]) is a Canadian [[comic book]] and animation artist who worked on the ''[[Gargoyles (comic)|Gargoyles]]'' comic and its spin-off, [[Gargoyles (comic)#Gargoyles: Bad Guys|Badguys]].<ref name="reviewBadGuy2">{{cite web |first=James |last=Hunt |url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=user_review&id=98 |title=Gargoyles: Bad Guys #2 |publisher=[[Comic Book Resources]] News |date=May 5, 2008 |accessdate=September 13, 2010 }}</ref>
==Career== Charlebois has degrees in Business Administration/Marketing from [[HEC Montréal|École des Hautes Études Commerciales]] and Arts & Communications from [[Collège André-Grasset]] and [[Collège Ahuntsic]]. She began her career at [[Cinar]] working on storyboard corrections on Arthur, then moved on to [[CinéGroupe]] working first on storyboard corrections, then as a [[storyboard]] artist on [[Mega Babies]] and [[Sagwa, the Chinese Siamese Cat]].<ref>https://www.imdb.com/name/nm4973845/</ref> While her storyboarding experience includes work on several [[video games]] published by [[Microïds]], [[Post Mortem (video game)|Post Mortem]] and [[Syberia II]],<ref>http://www.mobygames.com/developer/sheet/view/by_genre/developerId,133190/</ref> most of her portfolio is in traditional animation such as [[Arthur (TV series)|Arthur]] and [[Martha Speaks (TV series)|Martha Speaks]].<ref>http://portfolio.kantharasloft.net</ref>
After meeting [[Gargoyles]] creator [[Greg Weisman]] during the Gathering of the Gargoyles convention, she worked with [[Slave Labor Graphics]] as the lead artist in the [[Gargoyles (comic)#Gargoyles: Bad Guys|Bad Guys]] comic, and as a pickup artist on issue #5 of the main [[Gargoyles (comic)|Gargoyles]] comic.
