'''Shunpike''' is a [[non-profit organization|non-profit arts organization]] that functions primarily as a [[fiscal sponsorship|fiscal sponsor]]. The organization is based in [[Seattle]] and works mostly with artists from the [[Puget Sound region|Puget Sound Region]].<ref name="Shunpike Website">[http://www.shunpike.org/about-us/ Shunpike Website], About Us.</ref> In July 2009, Shunpike opened a satellite branch in [[Tacoma, Washington|Tacoma]].<ref name="Tacoma Weekly">[http://www.tacomaweekly.com/article/3516 Tacoma Weekly], Seattle’s Shunpike opens in Tacoma.</ref>

==History==
It was founded in 2001 by a group of young [[artist]]s and [[arts administration|arts administrators]] to support the local arts community. Since 2001, the organization has supported work by more than 1,000 artists working in live performance, film, literary arts, visual arts, and arts education.<ref name="Shunpike Website"/> Among its services Shunpike offers fiscal sponsorship for arts groups, acting as an umbrella non-profit that allows organizations to take advantage of the benefits of its [[501(c)(3)]] non-profit status without having to deal with the lengthy process of obtaining such status.<ref name="Tacoma Weekly"/>

===Spaceworks Tacoma===
In partnership with the City of Tacoma and the Tacoma-Pierce County Chamber, Shunpike is working on developing and managing this initiative to fill vacant retail spaces in downtown Tacoma with art and creative enterprise.<ref name="The News Tribune">[http://www.thenewstribune.com/2010/04/21/1156735/spaceworks-aims-to-fill-empty.html], Spaceworks Tacoma aims to fill empty storefronts.</ref>

